author: Min Zeng
title: U.S. Government Bonds Pull Back
text:
U.S. government bonds pulled back on Monday as investors took some chips off the table from a price gain at the end of last week driven by a disappointing employment report.
Looming new debt sales also weighed down bond prices. A $24 billion auction of three-year notes is due on Tuesday, followed by a $21 billion sale of 10-year notes Wednesday... To Read the Full Story, Subscribe or Sign In
